We recorded calls of one male at Bombuscaro (Provincia Zamora Chinchipe) on 9 June 2010, three males at La Pradera (Provincia Morona Santiago) on 10 June 2010, and one male at Comunidad San Luis (Provincia Morona Santiago) on 13 June 2010. The advertisement call consists of three to five quack notes (Fig. 12
A-B
). Mean call duration is 0.52 s (SD = 0.24) and mean rise time is 0.24 s (SD = 0.06). Sound frequency increases from the beginning to the end of the note; mean dominant frequency is 1855.81 Hz (SD = 148.08) and mean fundamental frequency is 884.89 Hz (SD = 105.52). Other call parameters are listed in Table 7.
